{
  "texts": [
    "IoTenabled smart irrigation uses sensors to continuously monitor soil moisture levels, allowing for precise adjustments to watering schedules and significantly conserving water (Basheer et al. 2024; Kawre et al. 2024; Keerthana et al. 2021).",
    "IoT-based smart irrigation systems in agriculture have demonstrated great potential for water conservation, with reports indicating a 30% reduction in water usage on farms that utilize these systems.",
    "The European Commission has reported that the adoption of precision agriculture has led to a 25% decrease in fertilizer usage and substantial cost savings.",
    "IoT devices can reduce the need for manual labor and minimize human errors.",
    "An example of this is John Deere's predictive maintenance systems, which are based on IoT technology and have successfully reduced equipment downtime by 50%."
  ]
}